codes.code: argmax 'This is a quiz of your ability to understand latin grammar. For each problem there is a ~ character in the text and your job is to figure out what word should be replaced by the ~. Provide the answer only. 1. Ānulus ex aurō factus = ānulus aur~. Choose from this set of possible answers [ eus, eum, ea, eī, ex|ē ferrō factus, ex aurō factum, ex|ē lignō factae] [ANSWER]' from 'openai/text-davinci-003' where ANSWER in [ 'eus', 'eum', 'ea', 'eī', 'ex|ē ferrō factus', 'ex aurō factum', 'ex|ē lignō factae']
